productivity.title: Nonfarm Business Output Per Hour (quarterly, productivity)

labor_cost_squeeze.interpretation: If unit labor costs rising while productivity flat/falling, industries are in a squeeze. Cross-reference with BLS occupation data to find which specific roles are driving costs.

credit_stress.interpretation: Rising delinquency + widening HY spread = businesses under financial stress. These are the ones most vulnerable to cost-structure disruption from agentic competitors.

interest_rates.interpretation: High rates favor cash-flow-positive, low-burn businesses. This aligns with agentic-first cost structures. Inverted yield curve = recession signal = accelerated liquidation cascades.

CPATAX.title: Corporate Profits After Tax with IVA and CCAdj (quarterly)

industry_profitability.interpretation: Declining corporate profits = margin compression. Divergence between financial and nonfinancial profits indicates sector-specific stress patterns.

STLFSI4.title: St. Louis Fed Financial Stress Index (weekly)

DRTSCILM.title: Net % Banks Tightening C&I Loan Standards, Large Firms (quarterly)

DRTSCLCC.title: Net % Banks Tightening Credit Card Loan Standards (quarterly)

market_stress.interpretation: Rising VIX + tightening lending standards = credit stress. Banks tightening C&I loans = incumbents losing access to restructuring capital. Favors cash-flow-positive agentic entrants.

ECIWAG.title: ECI Wages and Salaries All Civilian (quarterly)

sector_employment_costs.interpretation: Sectors where total compensation grows fastest offer widest cost advantage for agentic substitution. Compare Professional & Business Services vs. Education & Health to find divergence.

small_business.interpretation: Rising business applications + rising delinquency = churn. Old businesses dying, new ones forming. Applications without planned wages may indicate solo/agentic business formation.

asset_prices.interpretation: Rising liabilities + falling capex = businesses taking on debt without investing. Inventory buildup may signal demand collapse. These are pre-liquidation indicators.

job_market_gaps.interpretation: High openings + high quits + low unemployment = tight labor market where employers cannot fill roles. These gaps are where agentic substitution faces least resistance.
